---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const websiteJsonLd = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebSite",
  "name": "Online Supplements Singapore",
  "url": "https://onlinesupplements.neoi.jp/",
  "description": "Educational verification guide for online supplement listings in Singapore",
});
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Buy Supplements Online Singapore | Verification Guide"
  description="A calm guide to buying supplements online in Singapore: seller verification, label consistency, and practical red flags."
  path="/"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={websiteJsonLd}></script>

  <h1>Buying Supplements Online in Singapore: A Verification Guide</h1>

  <p>A calm, text-focused guide to evaluating online supplement listings in Singapore: seller verification, label consistency, and common red flags.</p>

  <div class="disclaimer">
    This site provides general educational information only. It is not medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment recommendation. Always speak with a qualified clinician about your own situation.
  </div>

  <h2>Why online listings need extra verification</h2>
  <p>Online supplement listings vary widely in quality and documentation. Unlike a physical pharmacy, online channels may lack consistent oversight. Verifying a listing before relying on it reduces uncertainty.</p>

  <h2>The online verification checklist</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Seller identity is clear (business name, contact, policy)</li>
    <li>Product information is consistent across listings and batches</li>
    <li>Full ingredient list is available (not vague "blend" descriptions)</li>
    <li>Amounts and units are shown in standard format</li>
    <li>Claims are realistic (avoid dramatic "instant" outcomes)</li>
    <li>Images match the written label information</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>When to pause</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Missing ingredient list or unclear amounts</li>
    <li>Aggressive urgency language ("limited time", "guaranteed")</li>
    <li>Conflicting product descriptions across sellers</li>
    <li>Overly broad claims unrelated to general education products</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Singapore context: pharmacy vs online</h2>
  <p>In Singapore, physical pharmacies operate under regulatory oversight. Online listings may originate from various jurisdictions. Applying the same level of scrutiny to online sources as you would to a licensed pharmacy is a reasonable standard.</p>

  <h2>Japan perspective: consistency over intensity</h2>
  <p>Japanese supplement culture tends to value stable, consistent formulations over high-dose or novel ingredients. This preference for documentation consistency is a useful frame when evaluating any online listing.</p>

  <figure style="margin: 40px 0 32px;">
    <img
      src="/verification-guide.png"
      alt="Buying Supplements Online in Singapore: A Verification Guide — infographic covering seller checks, red flags, pharmacy vs online comparison, and Japan perspective"
      style="width:100%;height:auto;display:block;border:1px solid #e5e5e5;"
    />
    <figcaption style="font-size:12px;color:#777;margin-top:6px;text-align:center;">
      Visual summary of the verification guide above. Educational use only.
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p>
    <a
      href="https://supplement.neoi.jp/en"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener"
      class="official-link"
    >
      Visit Official Neoi Supplement Site →
    </a>
  </p>

  <p style="font-size:13px;color:#555;margin-top:32px;">Educational content only. Not medical or treatment advice.</p>
</BaseLayout>
